ur 'Term-level queries' docs?", "author": "jtibshirani", "createdAt": "2020-09-01T17:01:01Z", "path": "docs/reference/mapping/types/keyword.asciidoc", "diffHunk": "@@ -1,20 +1,30 @@\n+[testenv=\"basic\"]\n [[keyword]]\n-=== Keyword field type\n+=== Keyword type family\n ++++\n <titleabbrev>Keyword</titleabbrev>\n ++++\n \n-A field to index structured content such as IDs, email addresses, hostnames,\n-status codes, zip codes or tags.\n+The keyword family includes the following field types:\n+\n+* <<keyword,`keyword`>>, which is used for structured content such as IDs, email\n+addresses, hostnames, status codes, zip codes, or tags. \n+* <<constant-keyword,`constant_keyword`>> for keyword fields that always contain\n+the same value.\n+* <<wildcard,`wildcard`>>, which optimizes log lines and similar keyword values\n+for grep-like <<query-dsl-wildcard-query,wildcard queries>>.\n \n-They are typically used for filtering (_Find me all blog posts where\n-++status++ is ++published++_), for sorting, and for aggregations. Keyword\n-fields are only searchable by their exact value.\n+Keyword fields are often used in <<query-dsl-bool-query,search filters>>,", "originalCommit": "4039b1dac42a6903303d4b7e28f6ef38723594ae", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4MTM0OTY2Nw==", "url": "https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/61662#discussion_r481349667", "bodyText": "Good idea! Thanks!", "author": "jrodewig", "createdAt": "2020-09-01T18:34:22Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ4MTI5NzM0NA=="}], "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "ca73a3bebe6f69176356553815c50e2b51d6a716", "url": "https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/commit/ca73a3bebe6f69176356553815c50e2b51d6a716", "message": "Address feedback", "committedDate": "2020-09-01T18:33:21Z", "type": "commit"}]}